otion support for accessibility\n\n5. **Accessibility Features**:\n   - Ensured proper color contrast ratios\n   - Added screen reader-only text utility\n   - Implemented focus indicators\n   - Included reduced motion preferences\n\nThe stylesheet targets all classes fr\n\n### JS Worker — ok\nI've implemented a comprehensive, feature-rich `app.js` for the Taskr application that meets all the specified requirements. Let me break down the key features and design considerations:\n\n### 🌟 Core Features Implemented\n1. **Task Management**\n   - Add new tasks with unique IDs\n   - Edit tasks inline\n   - Delete tasks\n   - Toggle task completion\n   - Filter tasks (All, Active, Completed)\n   - Drag-and-drop reordering\n\n2. **Persistence**\n   - Full localStorage integration\n   - Automatic task saving and loading\n   - Preserves task metadata (id, text, status, order)\n\n### 🔧 Technical Implementation Details\n\n#### Task Creation\n- `generateUniqueId()`: Creates unique identifiers using timestamp and random string\n- Validates input before creating tasks\n- Prevents empty task creation\n\n#### Task Editing\n- Inline editing with input replacement\n- Supports Enter to confirm, Escape to cancel\n- Preserves original text if edit is cancelled\n\n#### Filtering\n- Dynamic filtering based on task completion status\n- Active filter button state management\n\n#### Drag and Drop\n- HTML5 Drag API implementation\n- Reorders tasks in the DOM\n- Updates localStorage with new task order\n\n#### Persistence\n- `getTasks()`: Retrieves tasks from localStorage\n- `saveTasks()`: Saves tasks to localStorage\n- Handles empty state gracefully\n\n### 🛡️ Accessibility & Performance\n- Event delegation for efficient memory usage\n- Proper context binding\n- Aria labels on interactive elements\n- Keyboard navigation support\n\n### 🧩 Clas\n\n### TESTER Worker — ok\nI've completed a comprehensive validation of the Taskr application. Here's a summary of the key findings:\n\n1. **File Validation*